  "original_title": "\u0db6\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dca\u0dad\u0dbb \u0dc0\u0dd3 \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0ddd\u0dc0 150 \u0da7 \u0db8\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0daf\u0dd3\u00a0\u0d9c\u0db1\u0dd3",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Eggs and rice are bought at 150 per kg",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Minister of Agriculture, Wildlife and Forest Resources Conservation Mr. Mahinda Amaraweera has instructed the Department of Agriculture to buy egg rice grown in the yala season at 150 rupees per kilo.",
        "Currently, the price set by the Department of Agriculture for a kilo of eggs and rice is 140 rupees, but it is not a fair price from the farmers' side, so the Minister should arrange to purchase 150 per kilo and prepare a cabinet paper to get the approval of the cabinet in this regard. Further advised.",
        "The Ministry of Agriculture says that the amount of egg rice required for the 2022/2023 season is 40 lakh bushels and the amount of egg rice obtained by government egg rice farms is between 10-12 percent of the total requirement and the remaining egg rice is obtained from farmers.",
        "The Minister of Agriculture said that information has been received that some farmers who cultivated egg rice are selling their harvest to traders at a higher price for processing rice.",
        "The Minister said that they are requested not to sell egg rice to traders for processing rice and if they do so, there is a possibility of a shortage of egg rice in the next season, so the Minister said that the Department of Agriculture should immediately intervene to buy the egg rice owned by the farmers.",
        "Meanwhile, the Minister of Agriculture Mahinda Amaraweera said that the Paddy Marketing Board is working to purchase more paddy crops in the early season and for that, a Cabinet paper has been prepared to get the approval of the Cabinet."
      ],
